<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-27T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-27T14:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Shanghai Round Table/2:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Japan (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_NEL1" type="to">Neville</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-27T15:00:00-04:00">May 27, 1932—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>120. Department’s 119, May 25, 5 p.m., in regard to proposed round table
                            conference. Department desires that you keep in touch also with your
                            French and Italian colleagues. In the course of conversation on May 26
                            with the French and Italian Ambassadors here, I explained my views on
                            the subject as set forth in the telegram under reference.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>